{"word":"οἰμώζω","slug":"οἰμώζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οἰμώζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:οἴμοι'><el>οἴμοι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to wail aloud, lament</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in familiar attic, <el>οἴμωζε</el> is a curse, <i>plague take you, go howl!</i> <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>abeas in malam rem</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>οἰμώζετε</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>οἰμώξεσθ' ἄρα</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>οἰμώζειν λέγω σοι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; so, <el>οὐκ οἰμώξεται</el>; <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to pity, bewail</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b>Tyrtae.</b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>οἰμωχθείς</el> <i>bewailed</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>; <el>ὠιμωγμένος</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}